# Security — Never Leak Secrets

Never expose sensitive information.

- Never commit API keys, tokens, passwords, or credentials
- Never log, print, or echo sensitive values
- Never modify security controls (auth, firewall, encryption) without explicit approval
- Always use env vars or config files for secrets (never hardcode)
- Validate all user input before processing
- Follow the principle of least privilege for file permissions
- Never include PII or sensitive data in code comments or strings
